quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,And earlier We gave Abraham (instructions to follow) the way (which was) right for him and We knew about him
  21,52,"when he said to his father and his people, \"What are these images to whose (worship) you stick (devotedly)"
  21,53,"They said, \"We found our fathers worshipping them"
  21,54,"He said, \"Indeed you are and your fathers were in clear error"
  21,55,"They said, \"Have you (really) brought to us the truth or are you of those who are not serious"
  21,56,"He said, \"No! your Lord is the Lord of the skies and the earth Who initiated their creation and I am of those who bear witness to that"
  21,57,"And by God, I have a definite plot for your idols after you go away turning your backs"
  21,58,"So he broke them to pieces, except the big one among them, so that they might return to it"
  21,59,"They said, \"Who has done this to our gods? He is certainly one of the unjust"
  21,60,"They said, \"We heard a young man mentioning about them, they call him Abraham"
  21,61,"They said, \"Then bring him before the eyes of the people that they may bear witness"
  21,62,"They said, \"Did you do this to our gods, O Abraham"
  21,63,"He said, \"No! he did it, this big one among them, then ask them if they can speak"
  21,64,"Then they turned to themselves and said, \"Certainly you yourselves are the unjust"
  21,65,"Then they were made to hang down their heads (saying), \"You surely know that they do not speak"
  21,66,"He said, \"What! then do you worship besides God, that which can neither benefit you in anything nor harm you"
  21,67,Shame on you and that which you worship besides God ! Have you then no sense
  21,68,"They said, \"Burn him and (thereby) help your gods, if (at all) you are to do (anything)"
  21,69,"We said, \"O fire! be cool and (a source of) peace for Abraham"
  21,70,And they intended to set a plot for him but We made them greater losers
  21,71,And We delivered him and Lot (and brought them safe) to the land (Syria) in which there was Our blessing for the worlds
  21,72,"And We granted him Isaac and Jacob in addition (as a grandson), and each of them We made righteous"
  21,73,"And We made them leaders who guided by Our command and We communicated to them, \"Do good deeds and establish worship (salat) and give charity (zakat),\" and they were (only) Our servants"
  21,74,"And Lot, We gave him wisdom and knowledge, and We delivered him from the town which practiced bad things, they were certainly an evil people, transgressors"
  21,75,"And We admitted him into Our mercy, he was certainly of the righteous"